2026-03-16T23:38:19-04:00 | attempt-7 | area=evaluation | hypothesis=The shared `llm-rubric` is producing judge transport failures (`no last agent message`) that zero out otherwise valid compare configs. Replace it with deterministic structural checks for V1 compare shape, required git skill fields, and common alias/leakage anti-patterns. | classification=false-negative | result=KEPT | before=0/40 pass | after=14/40 pass | reason=This corrected a real benchmark problem. Promptfoo outputs that already satisfied the prompt and structure now pass without depending on a flaky local judge, while malformed no-skill outputs remain at 0/20.
